SIMPLE: undersong
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undersong
<hw>Un"der*song`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
burden of a song; the chorus; the refrain.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Accompanying strain; subordinate and underlying
meaning; accompaniment; undertone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the very [poetry] there often an <qex>undersong</qex> of sense
which none beside the poetic mind . . . can comprehend.</q>
<rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undersparred</ent>⟦br⟧
